      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you keep saying it's a symptom of the pain, like it's something to be \"fixed\" or \"managed.\" but what if the pain is the only thing that's real? people always talk about \"holding on,\" but it feels so cruel to force someone to hold on to nothing but agony. if there's truly no way to change the outcome, isn't there something more compassionate about accepting that it's over? shouldn't \"mercy\" mean letting someone finally rest?",
